This paper involves the development of a novel neural network architecture for predicting biodegradability, which involves both feature engineering and learned representations. This work is primarily focused on the application of deep learning in the chemical sciences, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and multilayer perceptrons (MLPs) for feature extraction and classification respectively, suggests that this paper may also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of deep learning algorithms for pattern recognition and classification suggests that this paper may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
